data.title: banan
data.titlle2: Banan is the name of the edible fruit of cultivated plants of the genus Banana (Musa); usually they mean Musa acuminata and Musa × paradisiaca, as well as Musa balbisiana, Musa fehi [en], Musa troglodytarum [en] and a number of others. Also, bananas can be called the fruits of Ensete ventricosum [en] (strictly speaking, which is a representative of another genus of the Banana family).

data.title: apple
data.titlle2: An apple is an edible fruit produced by an apple tree (Malus domestica). Apple trees are cultivated worldwide and are the most widely grown species in the genus Malus. The tree originated in Central Asia, where its wild ancestor, Malus sieversii, is still found today. Apples have been grown for thousands of years in Asia and Europe and were brought to North America by European colonists. Apples have religious and mythological significance in many cultures, including Norse, Greek, and European Christian tradition.

data.title: pineapple
data.titlle2: Real pineapple is represented in culture by a large variety of varieties, not only in South America, where representatives of the Pineapple genus grow, but also in all tropical countries around the globe.

data.title: mango
data.titlle2: A mango is a stone fruit produced from numerous species of tropical trees belonging to the flowering plant genus Mangifera, cultivated mostly for their edible fruit. Most of these species are found in nature as wild mangoes. The genus belongs to the cashew family Anacardiaceae.

data.title: avacado
data.titlle2: An important fruit crop. The fruits of the plant are also called avocados: their pulp is rich in vitamins and important minerals. In addition to fruits, wood is used, which is used for the manufacture of furniture and is used as a building material. Earlier in Russian, the names of alligator pear [4] and agacat [5] were also used to designate this plant.

data.title: Kiwi
data.tags: Kivi is the name of the fruits of cultivars of the genus Actinidia [1] [2] belonging to the species Actinidia chinensis (Latin Actinidia chinensis) or Delicious Actinidia (Latin Actinidia deliciosa) [3]. The plants themselves are large tree-like vines native to China [1], which is why kiwis are sometimes called “Chinese gooseberries”. In 2017, China produced 50% of the world's kiwi fruit [4].
